\formatnote{\chapter{Frame Message}}\indexi{Frame message class}


Frame message is a subclass of message handler, and inherits all the methods 
from that parent class. 


The class framemessage provides a creation procedure and a companion setting 
method.  Additionally, it overrides the following methods: 


\leftindent{DisplayString

AskForString

AskForStringCompleted

MultipleChoiceQuestion

CancelQuestion

GetCurrentString

InsertCharacters

DeleteCharacters

GetCursorPos

SetCursorPos

Asking

Advice}



\paragraph{Creating a frame message} \indexi{ \italic{framemessage_Create}}

\example{struct framemessage *framemessage_Create(frame)

struct frame *frame;} 


\leftindent{\bold{Class procedure description. }\italic{framemessage_Create} 
creates a frame message for a frame. 


\bold{Return value.}  A pointer to the frame message.} 



\paragraph{Setting a companion frame message} 
\indexi{ \italic{framemessage_SetCompanion}}

\example{void framemessage_SetCompanion(frmsg,companion)

struct framemessage *frmsg;

struct msghandler *companion;} 


\leftindent{\bold{Method description.  }Sets a companion for the frame 
message.} 


